    "$oid": "5b6e3e9de84f7e0014c4a51b"
  },
  "title": " The Financial Services Agency (FSA) of Japan, Has Put Up A Report Of Its Inspections Of Cryptocurrency Exchange ",
  "image": "https://i.imgur.com/hSlNyxK.png",
  "author": "lee simon",
  "category": "News",
  "intro": "the Finacial Services Agency (FSA) has to go with strict measures looking into new applications from exchanges hoping to get  an official operating license. Newly registered exchanges will be required to undergo on-site inspections at an early stage and the agency promised to look closely into their business model.",
  "body": "<p>On this day, The Financial Services Agency (FSA) of Japan, has put up a report of its inspections of cryptocurrency exchange operators.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From the discovery, the Finacial Services Agency (FSA) has to go with strict measures looking into new applications from exchanges hoping to get&nbsp;&nbsp;an official operating&nbsp;license. Newly registered exchanges will be required to undergo on-site inspections at an early stage and the agency promised to look closely into their business model.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to various&nbsp;investigations, the total digital assets of domestic exchanges took a massive leap&nbsp;to 792.8 billion yen which is equvalent to&nbsp;($7.1 billion), over six times&nbsp;increase within the space of just one year. majority of exchanges&rsquo; workforces are fewer than 20 people, meaning that one employee on average was found to be managing digital assets worth 3.3 billion yen equivalent to&nbsp;($29.7 million). The&nbsp;document of problems across exchanges&rsquo; business models, risk management and compliance, internal audits, and corporate governance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>FSA further highlighted concerns over insufficient&nbsp;anti-money laundering&nbsp;(AML) measures among few exchanges. the agency also stated it will continue to give priority to investor protection.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The FSA made a statement in july,&nbsp;it was considering changing the legal structure for the&nbsp;regulation&nbsp;of cryptocurrency exchanges, Lately the agency was&nbsp;&nbsp;restructured&nbsp;in order improve its handling of fintech-related areas, including cryptocurrencies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A self-regulatory body, the Japan Virtual Currency Exchange Association (JVCEA),&nbsp;formed&nbsp;in early March in order to develop and coordinate policies in conjunction with the FSA. Last month, JVCEA released a statement&nbsp;it would be requiring its members to place maximum limits on the volumes traded by their customers.</p>\r\n",
  "created": {
    "$date": "2018-08-11T01:40:45.413Z"
  },
  "__v": 0
},
{
