    "$oid": "5b998c74f486fb0014f0cac5"
  },
  "title": "Blockchain Research gets Approval from Indian Government",
  "image": "https://i.imgur.com/b0EU27K.jpg",
  "author": "Gourav J",
  "category": "News",
  "intro": "Cryptocurrency officially recognised by indian banks",
  "body": "<p>The Republic of India is on the verge of making the blockchain technology more accessible in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>India&#39;s Union Cabinet &ndash; an executive decision-making body composed of senior government officials and led by Prime Minister Narendra Modi &ndash; said according to Coindesk that it would allow the nation&#39;s Export-Import Bank (Exim Bank) to conduct research on distributed ledger and blockchain technology in partnership with banks in the BRICS economic bloc, of which India is a member, alongside Brazil, Russia, China and South Africa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The approval is ex-post facto, meaning that Exim Bank has already signed a Memorandum of Understanding under the BRICS Interbank Cooperation Mechanism, the Business Standard reported.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Specifically, the banks &quot;intend to enhance understanding of distributed ledger/blockchain technology, through the joint research efforts to identify areas within respective business operations where it may have the potential for applications aimed at enhancing the operational efficiencies,&quot; the Financial Express reported.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This brilliant move will also help further India&#39;s goal of developing a digital economy, Making operations in the financial sector more efficient is one hoped-for outcome of the research, according to the Express.</p>\r\n",
  "created": {
    "$date": "2018-09-12T22:00:20.693Z"
  },
  "__v": 0
},
{
  "_id": {
    "$oid": "5b9a0ab8f486fb0014f0cac6"
  },
  "title": "Star Xu Founder of OKEx Released From Police Questioning, Denies Fraud Charges",
  "image": "https://i.imgur.com/cqBob5o.jpg",
  "author": "Mark James",
  "category": "News",
  "intro": "Star Xu Finally Released From 24 Hours Detention",
  "body": "<p>OKEx Cryptocurrency exchange founder Star Xu formally hit back on September 12 at allegations of fraud after conflicting reports over why Chinese law enforcement summoned him to a police station for 24 hours Monday September 11, 2018.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to multiple local media sources, Star Xu, who is also the CEO of OKCoin, had faced problems at his hotel from a group of &ldquo;investors&rdquo; allegedly linked to WFEE Coin, a blockchain WiFi sharing project they said Xu held a certain percentage of shares in.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nAccording to <a href=\"https://cointelegraph.com/news/okex-founder-star-xu-released-from-police-questioning-denies-fraud-charges\">cointelegraph</a> who reached out to Xu with the findings, and the company also denied Xu had any equity involvement with WFEE.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Mr. Xu has no equity relationship with WFEE and its company,&rdquo; COO Andy Cheung said, adding:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nThough WFEE has acquired OKBC&#39;s [OK Blockchain Capital] and several other capitals&#39; investment, the afterward changes of WFEE white paper and team members have not been given notice to OKBC.&rdquo;<br />\r\nOK Blockchain Capital also tweeted that Xu is not a shareholder of WFEE.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Twitter, OKEx COO Cheung had stated September 12 that Xu experienced problems at a hotel, whereupon the police arrived and moved the parties involved to the police station, adding:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;While Star was invited to help with the investigation and those people was detained, they raised a fraud complaint against Star. Star stayed to clarify and then left afterwards.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Xu added in his interview that it was &ldquo;normal&rdquo; for citizens to exercise their right to make such allegations, and that he had equally fulfilled his &ldquo;duty&rdquo; as a citizen by cooperating with the authorities.</p>\r\n",
  "created": {
    "$date": "2018-09-13T06:59:04.360Z"
  },
  "__v": 0
})
